excerpt: Natal is the capital city of the state of Rio Grande do Norte, on Brazil's northeastern tip. It's known for its extensive coastal sand dunes and star-shaped Forte dos Reis Magos, a 16th-century Portuguese fortress at the mouth of the Potengi River. North across the river, Genipabu is an area of towering dunes with a freshwater lagoon. The Via Costeira highway links a 15km stretch of beaches south of the fort.
detail_description: Natal, the capital city of Rio Grande do Norte in northeastern Brazil, is a vibrant destination known for its extensive coastal sand dunes and historic landmarks. The star-shaped Forte dos Reis Magos, a 16th-century Portuguese fortress at the mouth of the Potengi River, stands as a testament to the city's rich history. Visitors can explore Genipabu, an area with towering dunes and a freshwater lagoon just north of Natal.
name: Natal
address: State of Rio Grande do Norte, Brazil

excerpt: 16th-century military fortification with cannons, a limestone embankment & chapel.
detail_description: Located in Natal, Rio Grande do Norte, Fortaleza dos Reis Magos is a 16th-century military fortification shaped like a star and perched on a cliff overlooking the sea. This historical landmark played a crucial role in defending the city and offers stunning panoramic views of the surrounding area. The fort's limestone embankment, cannons, and chapel add to its historical significance. It has been instrumental in repelling invaders and stands as an important symbol of Natal's history.
name: Fortaleza dos Reis Magos
address: Av. Pres. Café Filho, 1 - Praia do Meio, Natal - RN, 59010-000, Brazil

The Shopping do Artesanato Potiguar mall sells hammocks, pottery, and handmade sweets.

detail_description: Barreira do Inferno Launch Center, also known as Centro de Lancamento da Barreira do Inferno (CLBI), is a significant base for rocket launches operated by the Brazilian Air Force. Situated on the Rota do Sol in Parnamirim, this center focuses on launching small and medium-sized rockets.

excerpt: Catholic church from the 1980s spread across 2 floors, known for its modern, minimalist design.
detail_description: The Metropolitan Cathedral in Natal is a modern, minimalist church that contrasts sharply with its Gothic counterparts in the city. The only visible circular feature is the large altarpiece at the front, while all other elements are straight and plain. The cathedral's interiors are also full of clean lines and there is little ornamentation to be seen. This stark modernity is perhaps most evident in the liturgical ceremonies which take place here every week.
